cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel adaptive label regularization method for deep neural networks, which is mainly used for image recognition and text classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of regularization techniques such as dropout and batch normalization, which are commonly used in deep learning models, indicating a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
